  "texts": [
    "The reward-penalty mechanism in RLHF's second stage bears similarities to how humans form habits through impulserewards and punishments.",
    "With the involvement of impulse and intelligence, humans transition initial habits to conscientious actions, ultimately forming new habits and a more advanced self.",
    "According to Dewey (2008a), this progression constitutes moral growth.",
    "Similarly, LLMs undergo the same moral growth process through RLHF.",
    "It evolves continuously from initial habits (emergence and homogenization) into new, more advanced, and more aligned habits."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "According to Dewey (2008a), this progression constitutes moral growth."
  ]
}